header.gameNote: DUEL IN THE DESERT AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 98, Norfolk St. 82
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Josh Washington scored 23 points and Chris Daniels added 22 points and seven rebounds Tuesday night as Texas A&M Corpus Christi beat Norfolk State 98-82 at the Duel in the Desert. Washington made seven 3-pointers including a pair in the first two minutes of the game that erased a 5-0 lead for Norfolk State and gave the Islanders the advantage for good. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (6-3) went on a 23-6 run over the final 8:35 of the first half to take a 48-29 lead at the break. Norfolk State (1-8) got a game-high 43 points on 16-for-21 shooting from Tony Murphy, but it wasn't enough to stop the Spartans from dropping their third game in the four-team round robin event. Josh Ervin added 12 points and eight assists for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi, while Carl Nelson had 13 points.
